WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.240
this portion of scripture this morning.

00:00:02.240 --> 00:00:06.440
And we, of course, last week started a mini-series

00:00:06.440 --> 00:00:08.880
on preparation for revival.

00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:11.119
And in the message last Sunday morning,

00:00:11.119 --> 00:00:15.039
I sought to establish the need for revival.

00:00:15.039 --> 00:00:17.719
We looked at the book of Nehemiah in the first chapter,

00:00:17.719 --> 00:00:19.959
and we understood that Nehemiah requested a report,

00:00:19.959 --> 00:00:22.600
he received a report, and his response

00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:24.719
is really what we focused upon,

00:00:24.719 --> 00:00:27.680
and how he responded to the report that he'd received.

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.680
And I sought to provide you last week

00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:34.040
with a report on the church in America.

00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:37.560
And as we began to look at a number of statistics last week,

00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:39.639
I believe that it was quite evident

00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:42.919
that we are in need of revival.

00:00:42.919 --> 00:00:45.200
I said this, and it's worth repeating,

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.639
no longer should we shift the focus

00:00:47.639 --> 00:00:52.319
upon another group, another denomination,

00:00:52.319 --> 00:00:56.000
another whatever you want to label somebody as,

00:00:56.040 --> 00:01:00.279
in order to expose their sin or their failure.

00:01:00.279 --> 00:01:04.440
But rather, we must desire the light of God's Word

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:07.959
to be focused upon us as individuals,

00:01:07.959 --> 00:01:09.319
and in our local church,

00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:12.639
and acknowledge the need for revival.

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:17.680
We mention this, that revival, a very simple definition,

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:22.680
is God bringing His people back to spiritual health.

00:01:22.699 --> 00:01:25.040
We understand that as we acknowledge

00:01:25.040 --> 00:01:26.720
the need for revival,

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:28.440
that we could sit here this morning,

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:30.279
and we could say, okay, we acknowledge,

00:01:30.279 --> 00:01:33.160
we understand, we agree with the truth

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:36.879
that we need revival, now what?

00:01:36.879 --> 00:01:39.080
Thus, we've titled the message this morning,

00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:42.080
The Pathway to Revival.

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.040
The Pathway to Revival.

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:45.040
And I want you to understand

00:01:45.040 --> 00:01:47.000
at the very beginning of the message this morning

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:49.080
that the pathway to revival,

00:01:49.080 --> 00:01:51.919
there are many hindrances to that pathway.

00:01:51.919 --> 00:01:53.319
We find that there are many things

00:01:53.319 --> 00:01:55.599
that will cause the people of God

00:01:55.599 --> 00:01:58.400
to even perhaps acknowledge the need,

00:01:58.400 --> 00:02:03.279
but never step foot on the pathway to revival.

00:02:03.279 --> 00:02:05.680
Maybe they consider the cost,

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:07.500
and they say the cost is just too great.

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:09.800
They're not really willing to change things.

00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:12.559
They're not really willing to pay what the cost is

00:02:12.559 --> 00:02:14.679
to truly have revival.

00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:18.100
The hindrances to revival are many.

00:02:18.100 --> 00:02:20.179
We find that the enemy does not desire

00:02:20.179 --> 00:02:22.279
for the people of God to be revived.

00:02:22.279 --> 00:02:24.759
He is perfectly content and satisfied

00:02:24.759 --> 00:02:28.279
with God's people being apathetic and indifferent.

00:02:28.279 --> 00:02:31.080
He is absolutely just perfectly fine

00:02:31.080 --> 00:02:35.240
with the church of God in America being comfortable.

00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:38.160
God never called us to comfort.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:39.839
In fact, He said,

00:02:39.839 --> 00:02:42.279
"'Yea, all those that live godly in Christ Jesus

00:02:42.279 --> 00:02:45.520
"'shall suffer persecution.'"

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:49.559
We find that we look at the church of the Laodiceans

00:02:49.759 --> 00:02:52.320
referred to there in Revelation chapter number three,

00:02:52.320 --> 00:02:54.000
and they were a church that was,

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:55.259
man, they were comfortable.

00:02:55.259 --> 00:02:58.240
They had everything that they needed, quote unquote.

00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.440
They were apathetic and they were indifferent.

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:05.119
They had this perspective that they had need of nothing,

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:08.320
and really even the Lord,

00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:10.800
because the Lord was on the outside of the church

00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:14.820
that He bought with His blood, knocking.

00:03:15.699 --> 00:03:20.699
This morning, as we think about the pathway to revival,

00:03:21.899 --> 00:03:26.179
we consider the hindrances that are there,

00:03:26.179 --> 00:03:29.419
and we understand that there'll be great difficulty,

00:03:29.419 --> 00:03:32.139
but I hope this morning that we've acknowledged the need

00:03:32.139 --> 00:03:34.179
and we've determined that I wanna get

00:03:34.179 --> 00:03:36.300
on the pathway to revival.

00:03:36.300 --> 00:03:38.759
Revival is for the individual.

00:03:38.759 --> 00:03:41.940
Let me say this, revival is a work of God.

00:03:41.940 --> 00:03:45.380
It is God bringing His people back to spiritual health.

00:03:45.380 --> 00:03:48.860
It is a work of God Almighty, and the psalmist said this

00:03:48.860 --> 00:03:50.300
in Psalm 85 in verse number six.

00:03:50.300 --> 00:03:52.940
He says, "'Wilt thou,' speaking of the Lord,

00:03:52.940 --> 00:03:56.020
"'wilt thou not revive us again?'

00:03:56.020 --> 00:03:58.220
It's a work of God.

00:03:58.220 --> 00:04:01.020
We cannot manufacture the work of God.

00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:04.339
We ought not ever seek to manufacture the work of God.

00:04:04.339 --> 00:04:08.860
We simply desire that God would work,

00:04:08.860 --> 00:04:11.179
and this morning, we understand that revival

00:04:11.179 --> 00:04:12.259
is a work of God.

00:04:12.259 --> 00:04:14.979
I would say this, we're in a place and a position

00:04:14.979 --> 00:04:18.660
in our lives and in our nation where we come to a place

00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:21.559
of being desperate to see God work.

00:04:24.100 --> 00:04:25.859
We're desperate to see God work.

00:04:25.859 --> 00:04:30.700
The psalmist said this in Psalm 119 in verse 126.

00:04:30.700 --> 00:04:35.700
He said, "'It is time for thee, Lord, to work,

00:04:36.459 --> 00:04:40.700
"'for they have made void thy law.'"

00:04:40.700 --> 00:04:41.540
Think about that phrase.

00:04:41.540 --> 00:04:46.420
It is time for thee, Lord, to work.

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:49.059
We are desperate to see God work.

00:04:49.059 --> 00:04:51.500
We are desirous to see God work,

00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:55.420
and as we think about this pathway to revival,

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.619
as we seek to embark on this pathway,

00:04:58.619 --> 00:05:01.559
and we draw our attentions to what the prophet of God

00:05:01.559 --> 00:05:04.019
said in Hosea 10 in verse number 12,

00:05:04.019 --> 00:05:05.980
it's a familiar verse of Scripture,

00:05:05.980 --> 00:05:09.100
but I want you to notice in verse number 12 of Hosea 10,

00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.820
notice what the word of God says.

00:05:10.820 --> 00:05:14.440
"'Sow to yourselves in righteousness,

00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:19.220
"'reap in mercy, break up your fallow ground,

00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:22.660
"'for it is time to seek the Lord,

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:27.260
"'till He come and reign righteousness upon you.'"

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:30.160
Of interest to me in this particular verse of Scripture

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:32.339
is that little phrase in the middle of the verse

00:05:32.339 --> 00:05:35.660
where it says, "'For it is time to seek the Lord.'"

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:38.420
We mentioned that the psalmist declared in Psalm 119

00:05:38.420 --> 00:05:42.459
in verse number 126, "'It is time for thee, Lord, to work,'

00:05:42.459 --> 00:05:46.260
but here the prophet of God is saying to the people of God

00:05:46.260 --> 00:05:49.220
that it's time for you to do some things.

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:52.820
And yes, revival is the work of God,

00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:56.140
but we ought to be in a position where we are prepared

00:05:56.140 --> 00:05:58.619
for God to send revival.

00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:02.619
And as we look at this particular passage of Scripture,

00:06:02.619 --> 00:06:04.500
I'm gonna go a little bit out of order

00:06:04.500 --> 00:06:07.359
of how it's actually worded here in verse number 12,

00:06:07.399 --> 00:06:09.640
but I want you to notice as we think about this truth

00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:12.239
of the pathway to revival, I seek to get,

00:06:12.239 --> 00:06:16.279
I embark upon this journey, this path to revival,

00:06:16.279 --> 00:06:18.600
I must first of all, I would say this,

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:22.000
it is time to plow, it's time to plow.

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.799
Notice the verse of Scripture,

00:06:23.799 --> 00:06:25.519
it says this in the middle of the verse there,

00:06:25.519 --> 00:06:29.399
"'Break up your fallow ground.'"

00:06:29.399 --> 00:06:30.799
Break up your fallow ground.

00:06:30.799 --> 00:06:32.899
We understand the agricultural analogy

00:06:32.899 --> 00:06:35.660
that is being used here by the prophet of God,

00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:39.059
and we find that as he's using this agricultural analogy

00:06:39.059 --> 00:06:41.540
that he's seeking to establish spiritual truth,

00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:43.220
oftentimes in the Old Testament,

00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:44.940
you'll find that the people of God

00:06:44.940 --> 00:06:46.779
had hearts that were hardened,

00:06:46.779 --> 00:06:49.500
they had hearts that were not prepared for the word of God,

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.899
they were resistant, they were stiff-necked,

00:06:51.899 --> 00:06:53.100
they were rebellious,

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:56.920
and we find that their heart was not right with God.

00:06:56.920 --> 00:06:59.359
They would go through the motions many times,

00:06:59.359 --> 00:07:01.179
and they would bring their sacrifices,

00:07:01.179 --> 00:07:03.260
and they would say that we fasted,

00:07:03.260 --> 00:07:07.179
but God's saying, listen, I'm concerned about your heart.

00:07:07.179 --> 00:07:09.500
Your heart is far from Me.

00:07:10.820 --> 00:07:12.339
And we find that as we look here

00:07:12.339 --> 00:07:14.660
at this phrase of Scripture where the Bible says,

00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:16.339
break up your fallow ground,

00:07:16.339 --> 00:07:19.540
and we begin to think about the importance of our heart

00:07:19.540 --> 00:07:22.459
being ready to receive the truth of the word of God,

00:07:22.459 --> 00:07:25.820
being ready to receive the seed of God's word.

00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:30.700
We understand as we, again,

00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:32.779
speak of the agricultural analogy

00:07:32.779 --> 00:07:34.779
that is here in this verse of Scripture,

00:07:34.779 --> 00:07:37.940
we planted a garden this year.

00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:39.820
And there's never been a garden in the place

00:07:39.820 --> 00:07:40.980
where we've planted a garden,

00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:42.980
at least not for a long, long time,

00:07:42.980 --> 00:07:44.420
if there ever had been.

00:07:45.260 --> 00:07:49.140
And there was a lot of work to get that ground prepared.

00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:51.459
There was a lot of labor that had to go forth.

00:07:51.459 --> 00:07:54.140
There were, Joseph and I, he's smiling up here

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.399
because he was the one that was there with me working,

00:07:56.399 --> 00:07:59.459
and I mean, it was labor, it was work.

00:07:59.459 --> 00:08:00.299
Why?

00:08:00.859 --> 00:08:01.700
Because I couldn't just go out there

00:08:01.700 --> 00:08:03.619
and throw down some seeds and expect

00:08:03.619 --> 00:08:05.260
that they would take root

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:08.299
and they would produce some level of fruit for us.

00:08:08.299 --> 00:08:11.820
No, the ground had to be prepared.

00:08:11.820 --> 00:08:13.739
The ground had to be plowed up.

00:08:13.739 --> 00:08:15.660
There was work that needed to be done.

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:17.899
By the way, I couldn't just start with plowing.

00:08:17.899 --> 00:08:19.700
I mean, there was a lot that had to be done

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:22.299
in preparing that soil.

00:08:23.600 --> 00:08:25.579
And then once the preparations were completed,

00:08:25.579 --> 00:08:28.739
we could then plant the seeds, plant the plants,

00:08:28.739 --> 00:08:30.660
and then reap a harvest.

00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:33.659
But we understand this agricultural analogy,

00:08:33.659 --> 00:08:35.500
and we begin to think about our own hearts

00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:37.179
and desiring that we'd have hearts

00:08:37.179 --> 00:08:40.179
that are tender toward the things of God.

00:08:42.340 --> 00:08:44.460
Look over, if you will, in the book of 2 Chronicles

00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:45.900
in chapter 34.

00:08:46.820 --> 00:08:49.580
In 2 Chronicles chapter 34, God speaks to us

00:08:49.580 --> 00:08:51.900
about one of the kings of Judah,

00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:56.900
and really, Josiah here in this passage of Scripture,

00:08:56.900 --> 00:08:58.820
what a great man of God,

00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:00.979
what a great leader for the nation of Judah,

00:09:00.979 --> 00:09:05.900
the great revival that took place under his leadership.

00:09:05.900 --> 00:09:08.260
We find that it's in this portion of Scripture

00:09:08.260 --> 00:09:11.020
in 2 Chronicles 34 that God gives us

00:09:11.020 --> 00:09:13.260
some insight to the man Josiah.

00:09:13.260 --> 00:09:15.500
And of course, we know that he was just a boy

00:09:15.500 --> 00:09:17.700
when he began to reign.

00:09:17.700 --> 00:09:21.619
And he began to reign during a time in Judah's history

00:09:21.619 --> 00:09:25.580
of great wickedness and great depravity

00:09:25.580 --> 00:09:27.539
and idol worship.

00:09:27.539 --> 00:09:30.979
And we find that now, Josiah comes to the place

00:09:30.979 --> 00:09:34.659
and he gets busy and he begins to serve God.

00:09:34.659 --> 00:09:37.780
And by the way, we ought never overlook

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:40.940
the youth in our church.

